## Structured Knowledge

<!-- Stable build, edit, test, and project-convention notes. -->

- Use `uv run --extra dev python -m pytest` in this workspace; system `python` is missing and `python3` has no pip/pytest.
- Current layout is config-driven: edit source/output/models/prompts in `config/default.toml` or a dataset config; run seed/dev via `uv run python scripts/create_pruning_dataset.py --config config/default.toml`, run SVAMP via `uv run --extra hf python scripts/create_pruning_dataset.py --config config/svamp.toml`, and use `--upload-to-hf` only as the explicit Hub release gate. Logic lives in `scripts/llm_client.py`, `scripts/pruning_flow.py`, and `scripts/storage.py`.
- Accepted PT JSONL rows must stay compact per `docs/plan.md`: exactly `id`, `question`, `input_x`, `target_y`, `depth`, and `decision`. Internal pruning context and heavy audit details belong in pipeline helpers, rejected JSONL, and the dataset-level manifest; `decision.commit` is a deterministic `sha256:` revision of the decision-related config when no external git/model commit is resolved. Manifest LLM metadata must not include raw `base_url`; only record provider, model, temperature, max_tokens, and `base_url_configured`.
- Suitable HF dataset sources include the selected optimized-data baseline `lukaemon/bbh` config `logical_deduction_five_objects` field `input` split `test` with `answer_fields = ["target"]`, plus `ChilleD/SVAMP` field `question_concat` split `train`, `openai/gsm8k` config `main` field `question` split `train`, and `lukaemon/bbh` config `multistep_arithmetic_two` field `input` split `test`; preserve configured small answer metadata fields via `source.answer_fields`.
- Final-answer verification in `scripts/pruning_flow.py` must capture through line end and preserve decimals, including periods inside numbers.
- Default/local outputs are temporary R&D generation paths: `outputs/datasets/seed_dev.jsonl` for seed/dev, `outputs/datasets/svamp_baseline.jsonl` for SVAMP, `outputs/datasets/bbh_logical_deduction_baseline.jsonl` for selected BBH logical deduction, and `outputs/datasets/bbh_logical_deduction_gemma4_hf_preview.jsonl` for the HF-hosted Gemma4 preview. Final generated datasets belong in private HF dataset repos under `../reasoning-pruning-datasets`; private model/checkpoint repos belong under `../reasoning-pruning-models`.
- HF release behavior: configured `output.hf_upload_repo` alone is local-only; uploads require `--upload-to-hf`, fail early without a repo id, use the local basename when `hf_upload_path` is empty, and always write a local `*.manifest.json` next to accepted JSONL.
- Gemma4 generation path decision: do not use dedicated model/job scripts. Configure `[generation] provider = "transformers"` and run the normal config-driven runner, optionally inside HF Jobs: `hf jobs uv run --extra hf --extra gemma4 python scripts/create_pruning_dataset.py --config config/bbh-logical-deduction-gemma4-hf-preview.toml`. The Transformers backend must lazy-import torch/transformers, read `HF_TOKEN` only from env, apply the chat template with `add_generation_prompt=True`, move tensors to the model device, use `dtype=`, and decode only generated tokens. Keep LiteLLM for Gemini decisions and hosted endpoints; HF Serverless/Inference Providers, default HF Inference Endpoint runtime, and TGI were not viable for current Gemma4/custom architecture support.
